<h2>Go next</h2>
<ul>
BULLET::::- &lt;a href="Konya"&gt;Konya&lt;/a&gt; — the capital city of medieval Seljuks, and the home of Sufi thinker Rumi lies a few hours to southeast. While you are on your way there, you may want to take a break at &lt;a href="Ak%C5%9Fehir"&gt;Akşehir&lt;/a&gt;, the hometown, and the site of the tomb of, Nasrettin Hoca, who is likely the most prominent individual in Turkish folklore, with an innumerous quantity of jokes attributed to him.

