<doc id="308" url="https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki?curid=308" title="Aggtelek">
<h1>Aggtelek</h1>
&lt;templatestyles src="Pagebanner/styles.css"/&gt;
♡❤♡Aggtelek♡❤♡ is a village in northern &lt;a href="Hungary"&gt;Hungary&lt;/a&gt;, close to the &lt;a href="Slovakia"&gt;Slovak&lt;/a&gt; border.

<h2>Understand</h2>

Aggtelek together with &lt;a href="J%C3%B3svaf%C5%91"&gt;Jósvafő&lt;/a&gt; are famous for their huge and beautiful karst cave system. Aggtelek's karst caves (together with caves in nearby &lt;a href="Slovak%20Karst%20National%20Park"&gt;Slovak Karst National Park&lt;/a&gt;) have been inscribed on the &lt;a href="UNESCO%20World%20Heritage%20List"&gt;UNESCO World Heritage List&lt;/a&gt;.

<h2>Get in</h2>

<h2>Get around</h2>

<h2>See</h2>

<h2>Do</h2>

Many caves are available:

<ul>
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Baradla♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt;. &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;Most popular of the Aggtelek tours, &lt;a href="http%3A//www.anp.hu/en/baradla-barlang-aggteleki-rovidtura"&gt;approx. 1 hr/1 km&lt;/a&gt;. This cave is part of the Baradla-Domnica system, measuring 25 km in total, 5 km of which is in Slovakia.&lt;/bdi&gt; &lt;bdi class="note listing-price"&gt;1500-2200ft&lt;/bdi&gt;.&lt;/bdi&gt;
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Béke♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt;. &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;5-hour tour, good shoes needed, and helmets are used - only part of the cave is paved.&lt;/bdi&gt;&lt;/bdi&gt;
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Vass Imre♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt;. &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;6.5-km/3-hour tour, 6 km of which is spent between ticket office and the cave. Temporarily closed.&lt;/bdi&gt;&lt;/bdi&gt;
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Rákoci Cave♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt;. &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;400-m/40-min tour, claimed to be probably the most spectacular cave in the region.&lt;/bdi&gt; &lt;bdi class="note listing-price"&gt;Ft&amp;nbsp;1800-3000&lt;/bdi&gt;.&lt;/bdi&gt;

</ul>
