<doc id="349" url="https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki?curid=349" title="Aguaytía">
<h1>Aguaytía</h1>
&lt;templatestyles src="Pagebanner/styles.css"/&gt;
♡❤♡Aguaytía♡❤♡ is the capital of the &lt;a href="Padre%20Abad"&gt;Padre Abad&lt;/a&gt; province in the &lt;a href="Ucayali"&gt;Ucayali&lt;/a&gt; region of &lt;a href="Peru"&gt;Peru&lt;/a&gt;. It is a town in the &lt;a href="Peruvian%20Amazon"&gt;Peruvian Amazon&lt;/a&gt; situated between the cities of &lt;a href="Tingo%20Mar%C3%ADa"&gt;Tingo María&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="Pucallpa"&gt;Pucallpa&lt;/a&gt;.

<h2>Get in</h2>
You can fly in on one of Peru's national airlines to the City of Pucallpa and then drive by bus or by Autotaxi, or, for the more adventurous, you could try coming in on a bus from &lt;a href="Lima"&gt;Lima&lt;/a&gt;

<h2>Get around</h2>
♡❤Mototaxis♡❤ are the standard mode of transportation for Aguaytía.

<h2>See</h2>
There is not very much in the way of sightseeing in Aguaytía itself. That said, most attractions are water related and few miles towards Tingo María you can find the famous waterfall "Velo de la Novia" which is a nice place for a day trip.

