BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Waverley♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt; (&lt;bdi class="nickname listing-alt"&gt;The World's last ocean-going paddle steamer&lt;/bdi&gt;). &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;Round the island trips in summer months, from &lt;a href="Ayr%20%28Scotland%29"&gt;Ayr&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="Girvan"&gt;Girvan&lt;/a&gt;.
</ul>
&lt;/bdi&gt;&lt;/bdi&gt; 

♡❤♡From Campbeltown♡❤♡

<ul>
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Mull of Kintyre Seatours♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt;, &lt;abbr title="phone" style="text-decoration:none"&gt;☏&lt;/abbr&gt; &lt;bdi class="tel listing-phone"&gt; +44 7785 542811 &lt;/bdi&gt; . &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;Fast-RIB boat tours out of &lt;a href="Campbeltown"&gt;Campbeltown&lt;/a&gt;.
</ul>
&lt;/bdi&gt;&lt;/bdi&gt; 

<h2>Get around</h2>
Although there is a ♡❤♡narrow gauge railway line♡❤♡ once used by the miners, there are no actual trains on the island, so the only way to get around is by walking.

<h2>See</h2>

<ul>
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Ailsa Castle♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt;. &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;Ruins of 16th-century castle&lt;/bdi&gt;&lt;/bdi&gt;
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt;&lt;span id="Q4697091"&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Ailsa Lighthouse♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt;. &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;Automated, so don't bother knocking on the door!&lt;/bdi&gt;&lt;span class="listing-sister-icons"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/bdi&gt;
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Old narrow-gauge railway line♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt;. &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;From the mine.&lt;/bdi&gt;&lt;/bdi&gt;

</ul>
<h2>Do</h2>
<ul>
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Wildlife spotting♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt;. &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;Especially the tens of thousands of seabirds that nest here in spring and early summer.&lt;/bdi&gt;&lt;/bdi&gt;
<h2>Eat</h2>

Bring everything you want to eat with you, as there are no catering facilities on the island.

<h2>Drink</h2>

<h2>Sleep</h2>

Plans have been mooted to convert the former miners' cottages into luxury holiday accommodation, but this has been opposed by conservation groups, so there is no accommodation on the island.
<ul>
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡&lt;a href="Girvan"&gt;Girvan&lt;/a&gt; ♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt;. &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;Closest town with hotels and holiday cottage rental in surrounding area.&lt;/bdi&gt;&lt;/bdi&gt;

</ul>
<h2>Stay safe</h2>

Boats that operate trips to the island are generally open, or only partly covered, so it's important to take warm, windproof, waterproof clothing, at any time of year. The island is surrounded by steep cliffs, so care should be exercised at all times.

<h2>Go next</h2>
