<h2>Eat</h2>

The most well-known Akita dish is ♡❤♡kiritanpo♡❤♡. Kiritanpo is essentially a tube made of rice, generally formed around a disposable chopstick. It is often roasted, sometimes after being smothered in miso paste. It is also eaten in ♡❤♡kiritanpo nabe♡❤♡, a stew of sliced kiritanpo, vegetables, and chicken or fish, most commonly eaten during the winter. Of course, there are many non-local styles of food available in Akita City, including a wide variety of ramen and Indian restaurants.

<ul>
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Ebiya♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt; (&lt;bdi class="nickname listing-alt"&gt;えびや&lt;/bdi&gt;), &lt;bdi class="adr listing-address street-address"&gt;山王２丁目４−６&lt;/bdi&gt; (&lt;bdi class="listing-directions" style="font-style: italic;"&gt;From the Akita Prefectural Office, go a block east and a half block north.&lt;/bdi&gt;), &lt;abbr title="phone" style="text-decoration:none"&gt;☏&lt;/abbr&gt; &lt;bdi class="tel listing-phone"&gt; +81 18 863-5856 &lt;/bdi&gt; . &lt;bdi class="note listing-hours"&gt;M-Sa 11AM-2:30PM, 5PM-8PM&lt;/bdi&gt;. &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;Serves tasty tantanmen. Several Japanese magazines rank Ebiya as the second best ramen shop in Akita.&lt;/bdi&gt; &lt;bdi class="note listing-price"&gt;&amp;yen;500-1,000&lt;/bdi&gt;.&lt;/bdi&gt;
BULLET::::- &lt;bdi class="vcard"&gt; &lt;bdi class="listing-name"&gt;♡❤♡Kumari♡❤♡&lt;/bdi&gt; (&lt;bdi class="nickname listing-alt"&gt;枸茉梨&lt;/bdi&gt;), &lt;bdi class="adr listing-address street-address"&gt;広面字蓮沼９０−１&lt;/bdi&gt; (&lt;bdi class="listing-directions" style="font-style: italic;"&gt;From Senshū Park, take Highway 28 east for 2km. From the Lawson, go south 1 block. The restaurant is on the corner at the traffic light.&lt;/bdi&gt;), &lt;abbr title="phone" style="text-decoration:none"&gt;☏&lt;/abbr&gt; &lt;bdi class="tel listing-phone"&gt; +81 18 825-2010 &lt;/bdi&gt; . &lt;bdi class="note listing-hours"&gt;11AM-11PM daily&lt;/bdi&gt;. &lt;bdi class="note listing-content"&gt;An Indian restaurant.&lt;/bdi&gt; &lt;bdi class="note listing-price"&gt;Main dishes &amp;yen;1,000-2,000&lt;/bdi&gt;.&lt;/bdi&gt;
